	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Should Verant Remove Ability to Change Faces?</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=529972" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
I was reading the Developer's corner and Alan said that Verant was gonna remove the ability to change face/hair of existing characters. I think this would be a BIG mistake. I like the idea of being able to make my character look older when I get to 51...PLEASE post to the developer's corner if you feel the same as me!! The more people that voice their opinion the better.
<P>
Here is the link to the board:
<P>
<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000414.html" target="_blank">http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000414.html</a>
<P>
Braedan Eurevi<br>
Druid of the 29th Season<br>
Saryn Server
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
