Ok...here is my 2 copper.  Yes I agree with all you players that are POed because of the recent problems.  I had so many problems myself just trying to get started.  I even upgraded my video card...and i definately meet or exceed minimum standards...what do i get?  A lot of lag...sometime unplayable...hell, it even caused me to die and lose a level (   My rl friend still cant even get the game to work and there are some of you with worse problems than mine.  The point is this though... It is new and when its fixed, its gonna be totally awesome.  Any thing in this field, when new, has bugs out the arse.  Ask microsoft about that one.  And i would be willing to bet, that even if any of you that are complaining so bad had 20 years training in programming(maybe your programming trade skill is at 250+ :P ) you couldnt do any better...so be patient and stop b*tching. Seriously, its not the end of the world...or norrath for that matter.  When this is all said and done, you b*itchers will be the first to rave how awesome the new expansion is. And for those of you who cant play due to the fact that you have a 486 running win95...oh well...sorry about that, but what the hell did you expect that computer to do anyway. A pc like that could play many of the new vid games that are coming out.  PC's dont last forever and those lost there spark a half a decade ago.  I have a 1.4GHz pent 4 pc with 256MB ram, and a 64MB vid card and my pc is outdated already.  My advice is ask Santa for a new one )    Anyway...about the face changing...i do really like the idea of the ability to grow a beard or age my character, but in the end it is verants decision...they gave it, they can take it away, and if they do we will forget about it in a week...however, i will voice my opinion, because i do really like the new feature.  Anyway, gotta go see how the new moon of Laglin doing and maybe try to get lvl 30 back  )  see ya  and please be patient...no one is perfect, and when you do become perfect, then by all means, take verant over  )<BR>
